The documentation isn't very clear but it seems odd that if I want to reflect a vector `v` that I have to do `normal.reflect(v)` instead of `v.reflect(normal)`. Is that intended or is it a bug?

This affects both Vector2 and Vector3 in the same way (and the slide() function as well). Here's some GDScript to show the "problem":

```
    var v = Vector2(1,1)
    var normal = Vector2(1,0)
    var reflect = v.reflect(normal)
    print(reflect) # -1,-2 but expected -1,1
    var reflect = normal.reflect(v)
    print(reflect) # -1,1 is correct
```
